---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import RatificationMap from '../components/ui/RatificationMap.svelte';
---

<BaseLayout title="What Remains Unratified">
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>What Remains Unratified</h1>
    <p class="hero-lede">
      The United States signed a promise to protect your economic rights in 1977.
      It never kept that promise.
    </p>
    <p>
      The International Covenant on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights protects
      the right to work, to health, to education, and to benefit from scientific
      progress. 173 nations ratified it. The United States signed it &mdash;
      and stopped there.
    </p>
    <RatificationMap client:visible />
  </section>

  <section class="why-now">
    <h2>Why This Matters Now</h2>
    <p>
      AI-driven economic transformation creates winners and losers faster than any
      previous technology. The resulting bifurcation &mdash; between those who
      benefit from AI and those who do not &mdash; maps directly onto the rights
      the ICESCR protects.
    </p>
    <p>
      Without a binding legal framework for economic, social, and cultural rights,
      the U.S. has no structural mechanism to ensure AI's benefits reach everyone.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="paths">
    <h2>Explore</h2>
    <div class="path-grid">
      <a href="/covenant" class="path-card">
        <h3>The Covenant</h3>
        <p>Understand what the ICESCR protects &mdash; article by article, in plain language.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/gap" class="path-card">
        <h3>The Gap</h3>
        <p>Why the United States signed but never ratified &mdash; the arguments, the history, the cost.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/connection" class="path-card">
        <h3>The AI Connection</h3>
        <p>Differential diagnosis, knock-on effects, and the evidence connecting AI economics to your rights.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/evidence" class="path-card">
        <h3>The Evidence</h3>
        <p>Tariff impacts, AI investment data, conflict costs &mdash; the observable conditions driving urgency.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/action" class="path-card">
        <h3>Take Action</h3>
        <p>Contact your senators, use our advocacy toolkit, bring this to your classroom.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="framing">
    <blockquote>
      Human Rights, Nothing More, Nothing Less
    </blockquote>
    <p>
      Every element of this analysis represents implementation of rights 173 nations
      already committed to. Nothing here asks for anything beyond what the United
      States signed in 1977.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .hero-lede {
    font-size: 1.309rem;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-weight: 500;
    max-width: 36rem;
  }

  .why-now {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .path-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(18rem, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .path-card {
    display: block;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--color-text);
    transition: border-color 0.15s;
  }

  .path-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .path-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .path-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .framing {
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-xl);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .framing blockquote {
    font-size: 1.309rem;
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }
</style>
